2010-10-19  megacz  <megacz@usa.com>

	* Fixed timer request code in 'library/select.c' that was
	sending the request first and then clearing the signal it
	was waiting for... From now on 'pthread' programs should 
	work just fine and so all the hacks(delay bypasses or 'mst'
	watchdog) are redundant. Please note that other 'ixemul'
	branches and 'libnix' also suffer from this bug, which may
	mean that many network programs may work incorrectly under
	certain circumstances!

	* Added 'lseekw()' function that wraps 'lseek()' and so
	wrong offset control(whence) can be detected immediately.
	If program you are porting does not behave well and you
	know it does some 'lseek()' then add this: '-Dlseek=lseekw'
	to '$(CFLAGS)' and recompile. It will help, eventually.

	* Added 'strcasestr()', 'strndup()', 'strerror_r()',
	'strtok_r()', 'strnlen()'. 

	* Updated header files: 'unistd.h', 'string.h', 'signal.h'.

	* From now on 'libc' defaults to 68020, but code for 68000
	is still available.

	* From now on shared library is also available for 68060.

	* This is "repackaged" archive thus no version bump, but
	the date was changed.

2008-09-03  megacz  <megacz@usa.com>

	* Changes in 'include/user.h', increased library slots from 100
	to 1000.

	* Changes in 'library/ix_init.c', fixed MathIEEE library bases,
	they were associated with improper structures.

	* Added some useful/missing functions like: 
	'basename()', 'basename_b()', 'dirname()', 'realpath()',
	'localtime_r()', 'gmtime_r()', 'timegm()', 'fseeko()',
	'roundf()', 'truncf()', 'getopt_long()', 'inet_ntop()',
	'inet_pton()', 'gai_strerror()', 'freeaddrinfo()',
	'getaddrinfo()', 'getnameinfo()', 'strlcpy()',
	'strlcat()', 'strtoll()', 'strtoull()'.
	For now all of these functions are in 'libc.a', but some of
	them will be exported to 'ixemul.library' as soon as i find
	current 49+ maintainer and negotiate 'syscall()' values.

	* Updated headers due to new functions are as follows:
	'arpa/inet.h', 'arpa/nameser.h', 'sys/socket.h', 'sys/types.h',
	'math.h', 'netdb.h', 'string.h', 'time.h', 'stdio,h', 
	'stdlib.h'. Note: from now on 'sys/types.h' sets 'socklen_t' 
	and 'in_port_t' . 

	* Added some useful/missing headers like: 
	'inttypes.h', 'stdint.h', 'wchar.h', 'getopt.h', 'libgen.h',
	'sys/select.h'. Some of them are just "dummy" and dont define
	too much.

	* Changes in header files, fixed lack of comments beside 
	'#endif' directive in: 'sys/ucred.h', 'sys/mount.h', 
	'netinet/tcp_var.h', 'netinet/tcp.h', 'net/if.h', 
	'machine/pmap.h'.

	* (version.in): bumped version from 48.2 to 48.3 - please note
	im(megacz) not the official maintainer, so consider this new
	version unofficial build, i may bump it to some higher value 
	if there will be some complaints.

